In this article, the author discusses the progress being made in the fight against cancer through the Advanced Research Projects Agency for Health (ARPA-H) and mRNA technology. The author highlights the bipartisan support for ARPA-H and the success of mRNA technology in developing COVID-19 vaccines. The article also mentions the Cancer Moonshot initiative and the new ARPA-H program aimed at using mRNA technology to train the immune system to fight cancer, autoimmune disorders, and infectious diseases. The author emphasizes the potential of this technology to transform the fight against cancer and other difficult diagnoses. The article concludes by emphasizing the importance of unity and collaboration in achieving these goals.